# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/tmapi.git
cd tmapi

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Create .env file in src/:
# DB_HOST, DB_PORT, DB_NAME, DB_USER, DB_PASSWORD, SECRET_KEY, PORT

# Start the server
npm run dev

Tables are created automatically if they do not exist.
Swagger docs available at: http://localhost:5000/api-docs

âš¡ Features

User registration & login (JWT-based)

Password hashing (bcrypt)

Create, update, delete, and view tasks

Assign tasks to users

Task status: todo, in-progress, done

Pagination & sorting for task lists

Input validation for title, email, and due_date

Rate limiting middleware

Only creator or assignee can modify tasks

ğŸ“¡ API Endpoints
Auth
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/auth/register	Register a new user
POST	/auth/login	Login user, returns JWT token
Tasks
Method	Endpoint	Description
GET	/tasks	Get tasks (pagination & sorting)
POST	/tasks	Create a task
PUT	/tasks/:id	Update a task (title, description, due_date, status)
PATCH	/tasks/:id/complete	Mark task as done
PUT	/tasks/:id/in-progress	Mark task as in-progress
PUT	/tasks/:id/todo	Reset task to todo
DELETE	/tasks/delete/:id	Delete a task

All task endpoints require Authorization: Bearer <token>

